:We want to collect content directly on the wiki, so adding information here is always better than linking externally.
:Notable OSC projects should have their own pages. If a project has enough information or relevance—even if not widely known—it can also justify a standalone page. Similar or smaller tools (e.g. OSC-based chatbox apps) can be grouped on shared pages.
:This particular page should focus on official content. However, we can add a “Community Projects” section (like the one in the “[[Getting Started]]” page), marked with a community banner. That section shouldn't link directly to external sites but instead should point to relevant internal wiki pages. [[User:Usr 40be82e7-f7d5-4548-b314-3fc7b26d22ee|Usr 40be82e7-f7d5-4548-b314-3fc7b26d22ee]] ([[User talk:Usr 40be82e7-f7d5-4548-b314-3fc7b26d22ee|talk]]) 00:17, 2 April 2025 (UTC)